description: Initial (unsafe) primes of Cunningham chains of first type with length exactly 6.
comments: Special terms of A059453. Not identical to A023330 of which 1122659,2164229,2329469,.. etc. are omitted since have exact length 7 or larger. Unsafe primes starting complete chains of length 6.
example: 89 is here because (89-1)/2=44 and 64*89+127=5759=13.143 are composites, while 89,179,359,719,1439,2879 are primes. 1122659 is not here because initiates a chain of length 7.
author: _Labos Elemer_, Feb 21 2001
